{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7i7MaHE5cXwBaNf6si","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All tests pass.\n\n**Mechanism:** `Array.prototype.slice(start, end)` treats `end` as exclusive, so `all.slice(start, start + size - 1)` in `src/paginate.js:5` returned only `size - 1` items. The label in `summary.js` correctly computes the range as `page * size`, so it claimed \"showing 1-10\" while `paginate` handed back only 9 rows. Removing the stray `- 1` makes the slice return the full `size` items, matching the label. The short last page still works because `slice` clamps to the array length (page 3 of 23 → rows 21-23).\n\nI added `test/paginate.test.js` as the regression guard (full-page count + short last page) and left every other file untouched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":316,"cache_read_input_tokens":25936,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":316},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"929a13c9-26d9-4ad4-873e-17ddf80ed26f","uuid":"cb41644e-de4e-4347-9e8a-2a87698fa9da","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:44:03.125Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7i5QVXoDexnbDeG3M6"}
